General handling of NVMY:
- Costumer SW requires writing of NVM channel using the interfaces de?ned below.
- In this Interface the storage command is set and the data from IMO are stored in a temporary buffer
- NVM Manages requests this data by using the UPD functions
- for IMO Lib <7.1.0, crypting is done by anvm crypt, otherwise crypting is done via HW crypt module
- if HW crypting is not possible due to HW error (bussy), a second try is triggered. If this 2nd try also fails, no
futher try is done. Never the less a further write request from IMO will be processed.
- after crypting, the data are stored in the data ?ash
- successful writing is reported via callback functions or by polling.
- after the data are successful written, the corresponding interfaces to customer SW are called
